[The serotyping results of the virus involved are awaited. As indicated in the press release, 2 BTV serotypes are currently circulating in Europe, BTV-8 (France) and BTV-4 (Greece, Bulgaria, Romania, Hungary, Croatia). For a map, updated on 22 Oct 2015, of the European BTV situation according to serotypes, please see slide No. 10 in the presentation of the mission of the "EU Community Veterinary Emergency Team in Hungary" in relation to the bluetongue situation, 28-29 Oct 2015, presented to the PAFF Committee, Brussels on 9 Nov 2015, available at
http://ec.europa.eu/food/animals/docs/reg-com_ahw_20151109_pres_bluetongue_hungary_cvet_en.pdf.

In addition to the said report, national presentations to PAFF of the delegates of France, Spain, Romania, and Hungary on their respective BT situations are available as well at http://ec.europa.eu/food/animals/health/regulatory_committee/presentations_en.htm#20151109.

Culicoides activity, and consequently BTV circulation, are expected to decline as temperatures fall. - Mod.AS

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=3798888,109.]
